{{italic title}}
'''''Whonamedit?''''' is an English-language dictionary of [[medical eponyms]] and the people associated with their identification. Though it is a dictionary, many eponyms and persons are presented in extensive articles with comprehensive bibliographies.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Larner|first1=AJ|title=Who named it? www.whonamedit.com|journal=Journal of Neurology, Neurosurgery, and Psychiatry|date=2003|volume=74|issue=12|pages=1614|doi=10.1136/jnnp.74.12.1614|url=http://jnnp.bmj.com/content/74/12/1614.full|pmc=1757429}}</ref> The dictionary is hosted in [[Norway]] and maintained by medical historian [[Ole Daniel Enersen]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Huber|first1=Jeffrey T. |last2=Swogger|first2=Susan|title=Introduction to Reference Sources in the Health Sciences, Sixth Edition|url={{Google books|UJr9AwAAQBAJ|page=196|plainurl=yes}}|year=2014|publisher=American Library Association|isbn=978-0-8389-1184-6|page=196}}</ref>

